box1SquaresInfo.box1Square1PopUpText: Tesseract Risk has a concept of mulitple valuation scenarios to create parallel PnL data sets. Each scenario can use a different market data policy and different valuation models to give different stake holders different views of the market. The system then allows for the comparison of different valuations and can explain the differences.
box1SquaresInfo.box1Square2PopUpText: Tesseract Risk uses valuation scenarios to generate multiple, parallel PnL datasets - e.g. an intraday view, an official risk view, etc. It's reporting allows any two valuations to be compared, e.g. DTD change in official view or change in today's intraday vs yesterday's official. It's attribution feature enables risk reporters and front office to explain the change, e.g. change due to market data updates.
